text: In dark mode, the scrollbars are white. This is ugly - please make the scrollbars match the dark mode coloring and styling on all pages.

proposedTasks.title: Style scrollbars to match dark mode theme
proposedTasks.description:
Apply dark-mode-aware scrollbar styling across all pages. Use CSS `color-scheme` and/or `::-webkit-scrollbar` pseudo-elements (with fallbacks) so that scrollbar track, thumb, and corner colors harmonize with the dark theme palette. Acceptance criteria:
- In dark mode, scrollbar track uses a dark background (e.g., surface/background color from the theme).
- Scrollbar thumb uses a muted, contrast-appropriate color (not white).
- Light mode and system-default mode scrollbars remain unaffected or similarly harmonized.
- Styling applies globally to all scrollable containers (page body, sidebar panels, code/log viewers, feed lists).
- Verified in Chrome, Firefox, and Safari (Firefox uses `scrollbar-color`; Safari/Chrome use `::-webkit-scrollbar`).

taskTitles: Style scrollbars to match dark mode theme
